metadata.name: Yrsa #51
metadata.description:
Yrsa's viewers are met with a vast expanse of overlapping circles, each one housing a random number of inner circles. This composition immediately evokes the multi-dimensional and overlapping narrative of its Norse namesake, Yrsa. Just as Yrsa's life story is steeped in layered relationships and hidden truths, each circle in the artwork obscures and reveals, creating a sense of depth and mystery.

The varying number of inner circles within each main circle speaks to the unpredictability of life and the many layers of experiences and emotions we each harbor. Just as Yrsa's identity was both revealed and concealed through her relationships, the overlapping circles in the artwork meld into one another, creating a profound interplay of shadow, light, and narrative. This piece is not merely an abstract representation but a poignant exploration of the complexities of existence, the intertwining of lives, and the profound stories lurking just beneath the surface

metadata.name: Manu #90
metadata.description:
Manu
---------------

A collector-led exploration of minimalist imperfect line work.

Outputs are generated from a combination of the minter's address, their choice from one of 50 seeds, and options to adjust how the generated surface is presented.

Palettes are named after native New Zealand birds and range from the subdued to the colorful.

There are no especially rare traits so mint what you love :)

---------------

Controls:
S - Export as png
H - Toggle high resolution

metadata.name: Risonanza #387
metadata.description:
This series unearths the unique and energetic rhythms found within simple repetitions. Using distinct minimalist components, the algorithm patterns, contorts, and intertwines geometries to reveal rich and vital maximalist compositions. The explorations of Risonanza revels in the quirks that emerge through this process, seemingly with spontaneity. They invite us to identify and savor the underlying simplicity of a common language that resides amidst all manners of imperfections, randomness, and intricate complexities we perceive around us.

Embodying the equilibrium between simplicity and intricacy, these works represent the dance between the innate harmony of existence and life's unknown paths. This balance of forces provides a simple and joyful invitation to attune to the energetic, complex, and singular harmonious essence of each work of art – an embodiment of the eternal resonance that courses through the universe.


—————

TENDER x whitekross
September 2023

Risonanza is Italian for Resonance, and is a generative art series created by Alessandro Fiore (AKA whitekross) in collaboration with Adam Berninger of Tender.

—————


Key commands:

1 = 2000x3000
2 = 4000x6000
3 = 6000x9000 (Dependent on your browser limitations, tested on Safari (Mac))
s = Save at current resolution


License:

See LICENSE.md in live view for details.

metadata.name: Padina #202
metadata.description:
Padina collection focuses on the natural phenomenon where living organisms grow by adding layers of matter in a particular direction.
Formed shape resembles the algae genus Padina, but similarities can also be found in the world of fungi, like genus Trametes.

There are ten hand-picked color palettes, three composition types.
Multitude of variables control leaf surface details.
Each leaf consists of countless dots, which end up creating harmonic, or more chaotic patterns.


Double click: reset animation. 
Press "S" to save 4000px file. This can be slow.


Libs used: p5js, three.js

metadata.name: QuadTubes - Abstract Variations #224
metadata.description:
This piece features abstract patterns created using an algorithm I call QuadTubes.

It works by continuously stroking a set of quadratic curves that run through a set of points while rotating those points along a constant orbit.

This piece features 13 different arrangements and 11 different colors sets, so there should be around 20 pieces of each arrangement. Check the variations function to preview the different arrangements and styles.

The piece will slowly render and automatically pause after reaching its final form. You can press Space to Pause/Unpause the piece and let it run longer resulting in more saturated colors.

You can adjust the rendering speed with up/down-arrows or you can also load the page with
'&Speed=*'
at the end of the url to adjust the rendering speed (default = 25) and press S at any time to save an image of any state of the animation.
 
Initial minters will receive 10% royalties.


PLEASE NOTE: 
This piece was developed in and is best viewed in Chrome (100.0.4896.127). Moreover hardware acceleration needs to be enabled in the browser settings. There are still some browsers & devices that struggle with this piece, most notably iOS and Firefox. There is a fallback which is enabled in Firefox and iOS by default that works without hardware acceleration but produces notably different results in texture and color saturation (especially on iOS). You may force the fallback by appending "&noHA=true" to the url in live view and force the original rendering by appending "&forceHA=true" (Note you can combine multiple URL parameters with an "&", eg "www.fxhash.xyz[...]?Speed=50&forceHA=true").
 Please make sure that you have a device and browser capable of rendering this piece before minting.

metadata.name: Alien Signs #119
metadata.description: Famous in the galaxy curves are featured here. The ones that require only trigonometrical functions, thus accessible to all humanoids. Projections of pure math. Archimedean spiral, lemniscate, circle and occasional fish could be found. Black and white palette is rare. Occasional highway is crossing all the symbols. Press "e" to save image.
